<subSubSection id="C3776556EF903AF4FF78F814FA92FE74" pageId="193" pageNumber="194" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEF903AF4FF78F814FA92FE74" blockId="193.[136,778,1873,2070]" lastBlockId="193.[810,1452,173,437]" pageId="193" pageNumber="194">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEF903AF4FF78F814FEEFF835" bold="true" box="[189,298,2010,2036]" pageId="193" pageNumber="194">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFC4B2CEF903AF4FEFCF814FE0FF834" author="Stock, J. H." box="[313,458,2010,2037]" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the Sea Fisheries Research Station, Israel, 46 (Reports" pageId="193" pageNumber="194" pagination="1 - 126" part="27" refId="ref331068" refString="Stock, J. H. (1967) Report on the Notodelphyidae (Copepoda, Cyclopoida) of the Israel South Red Sea Expedition. Israel South Red Sea Expedition. Bulletin of the Sea Fisheries Research Station, Israel, 46 (Reports 27), 1 - 126." title="Report on the Notodelphyidae (Copepoda, Cyclopoida) of the Israel South Red Sea Expedition. Israel South Red Sea Expedition" type="journal article" year="1967">Stock (1967)</bibRefCitation>
considered that the material of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEF903AF4FF6FF832FDF8F7D7" authority="Brement, 1909" authorityName="Brement" authorityYear="1909" box="[170,573,2044,2070]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Bonnierilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="193" pageNumber="194" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arcuata">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEF903AF4FF6FF832FE4CF7D4" box="[170,393,2044,2070]" italics="true" pageId="193" pageNumber="194">Bonnierilla arcuata</emphasis>
Brément, 1909
</taxonomicName>
described by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFC4B2CEF903AF4FD26F832FC33FF09" author="Illg, P. L. &amp; Dudley, P. L." box="[739,1014,173,2070]" journalOrPublisher="Vie et Milieu, Supplement" pageId="193" pageNumber="194" pagination="1 - 126" part="12" refId="ref329073" refString="Illg, P. L. &amp; Dudley, P. L. (1961) Notodelphyid copepods from Banyuls-sur Mer. Vie et Milieu, Supplement 12, 1 - 126." title="Notodelphyid copepods from Banyuls-sur Mer" type="journal article" year="1961">
Illg &amp; 
<collectingRegion id="49A9F83FEF903AF4FC88FF63FC5AFF06" box="[845,927,173,199]" country="United Kingdom" name="Dudley" pageId="193" pageNumber="194">Dudley</collectingRegion>
(1961)
</bibRefCitation>
was not conspecific with Brément’s species. He designated this material as a new species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEF903AF4FCEFFF3CFBB0FECA" authority="Stock, 1967" authorityName="Stock" authorityYear="1967" box="[810,1141,241,267]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Periproctia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="193" pageNumber="194" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="falsiarcuata">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEF903AF4FCEFFF3CFC10FECA" box="[810,981,241,267]" italics="true" pageId="193" pageNumber="194">P. falsiarcuata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFFC4B2CEF903AF4FC23FF3FFBB0FECA" author="Stock, J. H." box="[998,1141,241,267]" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the Sea Fisheries Research Station, Israel, 46 (Reports" pageId="193" pageNumber="194" pagination="1 - 126" part="27" refId="ref331068" refString="Stock, J. H. (1967) Report on the Notodelphyidae (Copepoda, Cyclopoida) of the Israel South Red Sea Expedition. Israel South Red Sea Expedition. Bulletin of the Sea Fisheries Research Station, Israel, 46 (Reports 27), 1 - 126." title="Report on the Notodelphyidae (Copepoda, Cyclopoida) of the Israel South Red Sea Expedition. Israel South Red Sea Expedition" type="journal article" year="1967">Stock, 1967</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and placed it in a new genus, 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEF903AF4FC46FEDAFBC6FEEC" authorityName="Stock" authorityYear="1967" box="[899,1027,276,301]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Periproctia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="193" pageNumber="194" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEF903AF4FC46FEDAFBC6FEEC" box="[899,1027,276,301]" italics="true" pageId="193" pageNumber="194">Periproctia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This genus takes its name from the modification of the anal somite into the periproctal ring. We agree with this generic placement but we treat 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEF903AF4FCEFFEB4FC17FE52" authorityName="Stock" authorityYear="1967" box="[810,978,377,403]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Periproctia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="193" pageNumber="194" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="falsiarcuata">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEF903AF4FCEFFEB4FC17FE52" box="[810,978,377,403]" italics="true" pageId="193" pageNumber="194">P. falsiarcuata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a 
<emphasis id="B919EACFEF903AF4FBDAFEB4FAC9FE52" box="[1055,1292,377,403]" italics="true" pageId="193" pageNumber="194">species inquirendum</emphasis>
because was inadequately described and cannot be recognized.
</paragraph>
